The Tour De France is seen as Cycling's ultimate event. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Tour De France is seen as Cycling's ultimate event. Two budding cyclists from Khayelitsha have been granted the opportunity to witness the action. Cycling is not a popular sport in the community but Vuyo Mavuya and Vuyolwethu Nkomo have found solace in it. READ: Seriously injured Froome out of Tour de France They have been part of the Sports Trust and through a donation by Disfruta Sports Tours they get to witness the Tour de France. The two Vuyo's will be jetting off to France next week Tuesday to get a taste of the Tour de France action. eNCA reporter Justin Ford has more details in the video above.